rComments: Yi is a nice supervisor who is always there to give you some help if you are in need. She also often give you helpful suggestions and recommendations according her work/teaching experience, and helps you to make better decisions when faced with choices.
knows the material, very intelligent. tends to read off slides

Zhang is not a good speaker and simply reads off of her slides during lecture. She will give examples from her work experience but lecture is as dry as the textbook reading assignments. The tests are not graded hard but she does not do review sessions or give study guides. I would not recommend this teacher to a friend.

ISM 58 was pretty much kind of a joke. Which was a shame because it had a lot of potential of being a really awesome class, the overall subject was interesting. Zhang seems like a nice person, but you can barely understand her. I never listened in class, I spent 20 minutes on homework max, I never read anything. And somehow I managed getting an A.

Zhang genuinely cares for her students and their performance in the class. Her teaching style could use some work because 99% of the time you have no idea what she's taking about. The class itself is not too difficult however given that you're putting in the 15 hours of work expected.
